ou don't move on until you have 'em&quot;. If I had to use schools today I'd do Waldorf for Primary until Grade 8 (when Waldorf primary ends), and private High for the last 4 years. But be prepared to stay the course in Primary - they don't follow conventional methods or timelines. &#10;Very Important: If you love your kids, limit TV to one hour a week maximum, until the age of 14. Thereafter you can throw caution to the winds and double TV allowance to two hours a week. And don't buy them things. "/><type4:DocumentMetaData xmi:id="13" sofa="1" begin="0" end="796" language="en" documentId="4716" isLastSegment="false"/><types:WebArgumentMetadata xmi:id="24" sofa="1" begin="0" end="0" author="Arthur" date="08-02-2011 04:36 PM" docType="forumpost" origUrl="http://mybroadband.co.za/vb/showthread.php/302963-Public-school-or-private-school-for-your-kid/page3" topic="public-private-schools" thumbsUp="0" thumbsDown="0" origId="4716" notes="" title="Public school or private school for your kid?"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="39" sofa="1" begin="0" end="580"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="43" sofa="1" begin="581" end="796"/><cas:View sofa="1" members="13 24 39 43"/></xmi:XMI>